# git-safety.mdc

- Never delete stable code casually
- Never remove previous working implementations
- Never overwrite working code without understanding it
- Always preserve rollback paths
- Preserve backward compatibility unless explicitly approved
- Never rewrite release history in changelog.json
- Never use destructive git operations without explicit approval

## Project commit scope (built work)

- **One product per commit:** Application/product changes must stay within **exactly one** **`projects/<project>/`** subtree per commit (or per reviewable unit). Do not combine **`projects/<a>/`** and **`projects/<b>/`** in the same commit unless a task explicitly requires cross-project integration and records that scope.
- **Directory-bound only:** Product source, dependency trees, and build artifacts for that product are committed **only** under that product's **`projects/<project>/`** path (including a nested Git repo there). Do not commit product work at forge-os root; do not mix product commits with unrelated Forge harness changes (`.cursor/`, tracked `.forge/` tooling, root docs) in the same commit when it would obscure scope or rollback—split harness vs product unless one atomic, documented change truly requires both.
